WHPX Porting Log
================

This log tracks the remaining tasks required to fully replace the dynamic
recompiler with the WHPX backend.

Current status
--------------
- CPU backend abstraction in place.
- WHPX initialization and teardown work on Windows.
- Memory mapping and VCPU creation implemented.
- Register synchronisation on VM entry/exit.
- Interpreter fallback for unhandled exits.

Remaining tasks
---------------
- Implement handlers for WHPX memory and I/O exits so guest accesses are
  emulated without leaving the hypervisor.
- Support interrupts, exceptions and other CPU features through WHPX.
- Validate behaviour against existing regression tests on Windows.
- Remove the dynamic recompiler once feature parity is confirmed.
- Review documentation and build configuration for WHPX-only mode.
